{{News|July 14, 2017|Thank you!|A special thank you to all our wonderful contributors and translators who improve the state of our documentation and make important parts of our documents (especially the [[Handbook]]) available in non-English. Thank you all for your behind the scenes efforts! For visibility, the [[article blueprints]] (useful for creating new articles) can now be found [[#contributing|below]]. Happy editing!}}

{{News|April 20, 2017|Article descriptions and the 'See also' template|Your wiki admins have been experimenting by setting a [[Property:Article_description|Article description]] property in the body of some articles. The goal is to expose more data points and obtain an increasing amount of modularity across the site. Ultimately wiki contributors will eventually write less (and deduplicate) content by using templates to grep for data from other articles (such as the [[Template:See also|See also]] template). Properties come with [https://www.semantic-mediawiki.org Semantic MediaWiki], an extension to MediaWiki, and can be confusing, so be sure to read up them before getting too carried away.}}

{{News|September 21, 2016|HTTPS for links|As part of our effort to continually improve the wiki, we'd like to encourage the use of HTTPS for external links wherever possible. This is ''especially'' important for an article's [[Template:InfoBox homepage|homepage InfoBox]] link since it is prominently placed at the top of articles (and more likely to be clicked). Please verify the link supports HTTPS before substituting. Happy improvements!}}

